{"TopicId":197766,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Escape from Kerbol!","CreatedByName":"Singhnaut","CreatedById":207340,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-28T18:08:57Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Singhnaut","CreatedById":207340,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-28T18:08:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nexit the kerbolar system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-28T18:12:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou underestimate how easy it is to escape Kerbol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-30T14:26:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00223qLHXW3.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022166.67\u0022 height=\u00221200\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/3qLHXW3.png\u0022\u003EIt takes precious little Delta-V to do this. You can do the most direct route for about the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003Edv\u003C/abbr\u003E cost of a Mun landing and return. Maybe a tiny bit more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-11-22T15:48:05Z\u0022 title=\u002211/22/2020 03:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 22, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Pds314\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-30T14:57:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223875093\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221604067981\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pds314\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n30 minutes ago, Pds314 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt takes precious little Delta-V to do this. You can do the most direct route for less than a Mun landing and return.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed, as far as I know all it takes is a Jool gravity assist.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GuessingEveryDay","CreatedById":203507,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-30T14:59:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust do what the Voyager probes did. Swing around the planet the right way, and it\u0027ll take care of the rest. Be careful not to go around the moons, or you\u0027ll just end up around Jool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-31T00:25:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223875103\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221604069838\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed, as far as I know all it takes is a Jool gravity assist.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell in principle Kerbin and Eve assists could do it I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"vyznev","CreatedById":90620,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-31T01:09:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223875308\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221604103921\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270014\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pds314\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n32 minutes ago, Pds314 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell in principle Kerbin and Eve assists could do it I think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure, if you use enough of them. And in any case, it\u0027s well known that you can use Kerbin and Eve assists to get to Jool, which will then let you escape Kerbol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn fact, I\u0027m pretty sure that if you can get from Kerbin to a Mun encounter, the rest of the trip can be done with arbitrarily low delta-v if you just have enough patience and fine control. Basically, you\u0027d use a Mun gravity assist to get out of Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E, then repeated assists from Kerbin and/or the Mun to get to Eve, then Eve and Kerbin assists to get to Jool, and then a single Jool assist should be enough to reach escape velocity. It\u0027s going to take a while, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if there could be an interesting optimization challenge here. Maybe something like minimizing launch cost multiplied by the time to reach some given distance from Kerbol?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"L1L1TH","CreatedById":207891,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-31T01:19:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou cannot really exit the Kerbolar System, It\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E is inifnite. Though theres a point where your trajectory shows itself going backwards. Im not sure but I think its pretty much impossible to escape the system\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Martian Emigrant","CreatedById":158362,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-31T04:28:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe following picture is from a time I broke the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy probe kinda was propelled at something like warp 3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Np3il2Y.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002297.75\u0022 height=\u0022733\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Np3il2Y.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you get far enough with enough speed the game won\u0027t show an orbit anymore but it is still in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of Kerbol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt shows where you came from and doesn\u0027t seems able to predict where you will be anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Nav ball still shows your attitude relative to kerbol and your \u0022Altitude\u0022 is still referencing Kerbol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are no other stars. There is no Galactic \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E to enter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nME\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPS just noticed that \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/207891-tr_hydra/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022207891\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/207891-tr_hydra/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TR_HyDra\u003C/a\u003E is new. Welcome to the forum.......And Hail I guess.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-10-31T04:33:59Z\u0022 title=\u002210/31/2020 04:33  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 31, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Martian Emigrant\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-31T05:11:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223875321\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221604107158\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207891\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TR_HyDra\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, TR_HyDra said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou cannot really exit the Kerbolar System, It\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is inifnite. Though theres a point where your trajectory shows itself going backwards. Im not sure but I think its pretty much impossible to escape the system\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. It\u0027s definitely possible to escape in the sense that you will never fall back. All you need to do is reach the local escape velocity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223875318\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221604106590\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290620\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022vyznev\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, vyznev said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure, if you use enough of them. And in any case, it\u0027s well known that you can use Kerbin and Eve assists to get to Jool, which will then let you escape Kerbol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn fact, I\u0027m pretty sure that if you can get from Kerbin to a Mun encounter, the rest of the trip can be done with arbitrarily low delta-v if you just have enough patience and fine control. Basically, you\u0027d use a Mun gravity assist to get out of Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, then repeated assists from Kerbin and/or the Mun to get to Eve, then Eve and Kerbin assists to get to Jool, and then a single Jool assist should be enough to reach escape velocity. It\u0027s going to take a while, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if there could be an interesting optimization challenge here. Maybe something like minimizing launch cost multiplied by the time to reach some given distance from Kerbol?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat would be an interesting challenge but I suspect the result would not be to use maximum gravity assists but a mix of cost reduction techniques and gravity assists.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-31T05:30:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah I just managed to escape Kerbol with a Kerbal on a $2300 Mun rocket and no gravity assists, although I did have to dip into the Kerbal Jetpack a bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-10-31T06:42:01Z\u0022 title=\u002210/31/2020 06:42  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 31, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Pds314\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Singhnaut","CreatedById":207340,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-02T16:29:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223874141\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221603908759\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/28/2020 at 1:12 PM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou underestimate how easy it is to escape Kerbol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI kno, its for noobs\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nwhen I launched a sat from sun and exited kernel\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223875370\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221604118530\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022158362\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Martian Emigrant\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/30/2020 at 11:28 PM, Martian Emigrant said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey all.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe following picture is from a time I broke the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy probe kinda was propelled at something like warp 3.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Np3il2Y.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Np3il2Y.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002297.75\u0022 height=\u0022733\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/Np3il2Y.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen you get far enough with enough speed the game won\u0027t show an orbit anymore but it is still in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of Kerbol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt shows where you came from and doesn\u0027t seems able to predict where you will be anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Nav ball still shows your attitude relative to kerbol and your \u0022Altitude\u0022 is still referencing Kerbol.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are no other stars. There is no Galactic \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E to enter.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nME\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPS just noticed that \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/207891-tr_hydra/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022207891\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/207891-tr_hydra/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@TR_HyDra\u003C/a\u003E is new. Welcome to the forum.......And Hail I guess.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nits like a nicer kraken, I\u0027ve encountered that too!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-02T16:44:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223876148\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221604334578\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207340\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Singhnaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Singhnaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223874141\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221603908759\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/28/2020 at 6:12 PM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou underestimate how easy it is to escape Kerbol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI kno, its for noobs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe epitome of being a newbie is accidentally making a rocket powerful enough to escape Kerbol\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"camacju","CreatedById":207172,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-02T16:49:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the record for lowest \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E is 873 m/s using many Kerbin-Mun assists. Theoretical minimum is 840 m/s because that\u0027s the minimum you need to escape from Kerbin. And if you can get to Eve you can bounce between Kerbin and Eve until you escape Kerbol, for practically no delta-v cost at all. I bet escaping Kerbol using less than 900 m/s is possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Misguided Kerbal","CreatedById":203209,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-04T19:02:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s pretty easy, in my opinion. Take a probe, strap it onto a launcher with a wolfhound second stage, and boom. Out of the system. See (shameless self plug) example here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022203209\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8448997141\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/192962-kasa-complete/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3811943\u0026amp;embedComment=3811943\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:261px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"L1L1TH","CreatedById":207891,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-04T21:57:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158362-martian-emigrant/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022158362\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/158362-martian-emigrant/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Martian Emigrant\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Thank you for that! I\u0027ll enjoy being hailed here haha. No actually\u00A0 if you refer to the mythological Hydra, (because you were saying hail) I didnt take that name from there. My inspiration was from one of Pluto\u0027s moons!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dat Kerbal Dude","CreatedById":206145,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-05T00:01:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nif you want to get the hell out of the Kerbolar System, follow this tutorial:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIngredients:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\na legal KSP install\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\na Core Stage Booster.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nA Upper stage Booster.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAnother Booster.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nMOOOODSDSD.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nOptional Ingredients:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nMOAR BOOSTERSADSDAS DWAAS SA.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nmore stages.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nstep 1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstall ksp,and blah blah blah pay the FBI a couple of...\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Emony.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003Estep 1.25.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003Euninstall Orbiter Spavce simulator because idk.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003Estep 1.5.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ci\u003Edoubledouble click KSP_x64 or x86 or wathev the exe\u00A0name is.\u003C/i\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ci\u003Estep 1.75.\u003C/i\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwait trillions of years for ksp to load.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nstep 2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDesign your rocket with your damn imagination.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin case you ddon\u0027t have imagination(like me),copy one of the following rockets:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022N1 1M1 mockup on the launch pad at the Baikonur Cosmodrome in late 1967.jpg\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022163.69\u0022 height=\u0022360\u0022 srcset=\u0022//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/N1_1M1_mockup_on_the_launch_pad_at_the_Baikonur_Cosmodrome_in_late_1967.jpg/330px-N1_1M1_mockup_on_the_launch_pad_at_the_Baikonur_Cosmodrome_in_late_1967.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/N1_1M1_mockup_on_the_launch_pad_at_the_Baikonur_Cosmodrome_in_late_1967.jpg/440px-N1_1M1_mockup_on_the_launch_pad_at_the_Baikonur_Cosmodrome_in_late_1967.jpg 2x\u0022 style=\u0022width:168px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022220\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/N1_1M1_mockup_on_the_launch_pad_at_the_Baikonur_Cosmodrome_in_late_1967.jpg/220px-N1_1M1_mockup_on_the_launch_pad_at_the_Baikonur_Cosmodrome_in_late_1967.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Apollo 11 Launch - GPN-2000-000630.jpg\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022125.00\u0022 height=\u0022275\u0022 srcset=\u0022//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Apollo_11_Launch_-_GPN-2000-000630.jpg/330px-Apollo_11_Launch_-_GPN-2000-000630.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Apollo_11_Launch_-_GPN-2000-000630.jpg/440px-Apollo_11_Launch_-_GPN-2000-000630.jpg 2x\u0022 width=\u0022220\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/Apollo_11_Launch_-_GPN-2000-000630.jpg/220px-Apollo_11_Launch_-_GPN-2000-000630.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Titan4B on Launch Complex 40.jpg\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022150.27\u0022 height=\u0022330\u0022 srcset=\u0022//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Titan4B_on_Launch_Complex_40.jpg/330px-Titan4B_on_Launch_Complex_40.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Titan4B_on_Launch_Complex_40.jpg/440px-Titan4B_on_Launch_Complex_40.jpg 2x\u0022 style=\u0022width:183px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u0022220\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Titan4B_on_Launch_Complex_40.jpg/220px-Titan4B_on_Launch_Complex_40.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022152px-NewHorizons_Rocket_Bly.jpg\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022133.55\u0022 height=\u0022203\u0022 srcset=\u0022//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/NewHorizons_Rocket_Bly.jpg/228px-NewHorizons_Rocket_Bly.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/NewHorizons_Rocket_Bly.jpg/304px-NewHorizons_Rocket_Bly.jpg 2x\u0022 width=\u0022152\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/NewHorizons_Rocket_Bly.jpg/152px-NewHorizons_Rocket_Bly.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand now the final step:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlaunch that Rocket you\u0027ve builded in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, fire dah engines,once you have reached into spavce,fire again the upper stage you\u0027ve designed,blah blah blah,do orbital maneuvering,and once your spacecraft has encountered the M\u00FCn,make sure you\u0027re not into a impact trayectory on the M\u00FCn,modify your \u0022Sub-Orbital\u0022 Trayectory into a \u0022Orbital\u0022 Flyby Trayectory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit should look\u00A0like this(ignore these\u00A0damn Joolian moons of the gif picture):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022220px-Animation_of_Pioneer_11_trajectory\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022165\u0022 width=\u0022220\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7d/Animation_of_Pioneer_11_trajectory_around_Jupiter.gif/220px-Animation_of_Pioneer_11_trajectory_around_Jupiter.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nfire your another Innertial Upperian booster once you have reached the periapsis(ergo,the most closest aproach point) of the M\u00FCn.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nblah blah blah,do wathev stuff on InterKerbollar spapcve.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Comic Sans MS\u0027, cursive;\u0022\u003E\u003Cem\u003Ethe end.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnow, if you will,i\u0027ll bury myself on the Kremlin wall Necropolis forever,bye.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003Ewaht kind of abominability and disgusting tutorial i\u0027ve made...\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JebIsBestPilot","CreatedById":207984,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-05T19:26:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou CAN just attach to an interplanetary comet under the right circumstances, like it not getting captured in Kerbol\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pds314","CreatedById":70014,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-11-22T15:47:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223876155\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022197766\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221604335472\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/2/2020 at 8:44 AM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe epitome of being a newbie is accidentally making a rocket powerful enough to escape Kerbol\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/kerbal-forum-uploads/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah in fact I would say it\u0027s basically a viable noob challenge to AVOID that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022go to Minmus/Mun/Gilly/Ike/wherever in a rocket that\u0027s physically incapable of directly burning to Kerbol escape from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would say Duna as well but I\u0027m honestly not sure that\u0027s actually possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}